{
  "texts": [
    "As of May 2023, Bard has transitioned to PaLM-2, whose dimensions remain undisclosed but are smaller than its predecessor PaLM, which had 540 billion parameters, due to compute-optimal scaling of parameter size.",
    "Chowdhery et al. [5] noted that in the development of their 540-billion parameter Pathways Language Model (PaLM) the effect of the model scale does not seem to be saturated yet.",
    "According to a leak the GPT-4 model has 1760 billion parameters, but it is not officially disclosed.A key challenge for LLM development is the curation and preparation of datasets.",
    "For instance, GPT-3 utilized a diverse mix of sources, including WebText2 and Wikipedia, totaling 499 • 10 9 tokens [3].",
    "Similarly, PaLM was trained on 780 • 10 9 tokens from various sources, such as Github and social-media conversations [5]."
  ]
}